
======================================================================
  PART 1: THE Q(√5) TOWER
======================================================================

Second-order recurrence f(n) = f(n-1) + x·f(n-2)
Discriminant Δ = 1 + 4x
Roots = (1 ± √Δ) / 2

x values where Δ involves √5 (i.e., Δ = 5m² for integer m):
  x = (5m² - 1)/4, requiring m ≡ 1 or 3 (mod 4) for integer x

   m        x          Δ           √Δ           r₊           r₋      r₊ in terms of φ
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
