======================================================================
  PART 7: MASTER POLYNOMIAL SPECIALIZATIONS AT x=2
======================================================================

Master polynomial: z^{k+1} - (1+x)z^k + x^k = 0
At x=2: z^{k+1} - 3z^k + 2^k = 0

k=2: Q_2 coefficients = [1, -1, -2]
     remainder = 0 (should be 0)
     dom root of Q_2 = 2.0000000000 (→ 3 as k→∞)

k=3: Q_3 coefficients = [1, -1, -2, -4]
     remainder = 0 (should be 0)
     dom root of Q_3 = 2.4675038571 (→ 3 as k→∞)

k=4: Q_4 coefficients = [1, -1, -2, -4, -8]
     remainder = 0 (should be 0)
     dom root of Q_4 = 2.6980689131 (→ 3 as k→∞)

k=5: Q_5 coefficients = [1, -1, -2, -4, -8, -16]
     remainder = 0 (should be 0)
     dom root of Q_5 = 2.8208299300 (→ 3 as k→∞)

k=6: Q_6 coefficients = [1, -1, -2, -4, -8, -16, -32]
     remainder = 0 (should be 0)
