======================================================================
  PART 8: 5-CYCLE CONTRIBUTION TO H AT n=5
======================================================================

At n=5: H = 1 + 2α₁ where α₁ = dc3 + dc5
(No α₂ possible since 3+3=6 > 5)

H = 1 + 2(dc3 + dc5) verified: 1024/1024 correct

Relative contribution of 5-cycles vs 3-cycles to α₁:
  Total dc3 across all tournaments: 2560
  Total dc5 across all tournaments: 768
  Total α₁ = dc3+dc5: 3328
  dc5/α₁ = 0.2308
  dc3/α₁ = 0.7692
  dc5/dc3 = 0.3000

H contribution analysis:
  Mean H = 7.5000
  Mean contribution from dc3: 2·mean(dc3) = 5.0000
  Mean contribution from dc5: 2·mean(dc5) = 1.5000
  Fraction of (H-1) from 5-cycles: 0.2308

